      <p>
        To get a better understanding of the purpose of the measures and how it
        addresses pressures, including pressures not identified under Article
        8<em>(1)</em> on different parts of the ecosystem, the assessor should
        check the schema fields: &lsquo;MeasureDescription&rsquo; (free text)
        and &lsquo;MeasurePurpose&rsquo; where the MS is required to specify
        whether the measure:
      </p>
      <p><br /></p>
      <ul>
        <ul>
          <ul>
            <ul>
              <ul>
                <ol type="a">
                  <li>
                    <p lang="fr-BE">
                      Directly
                      <strong>prevent further inputs of pressure</strong> (e.g.
                      by managing the source activity)
                    </p>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <p lang="fr-BE">
                      Directly
                      <strong>reduce existing levels of the pressure</strong> in
                      the marine environment (e.g. removal of litter or oil
                      spill clean-up)
                    </p>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <p lang="fr-BE">
                      Indirectly
                      <strong>prevent further inputs of pressure</strong> (e.g.
                      by governance mechanisms, financial incentives, awareness
                      campaigns)
                    </p>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <p lang="fr-BE">
                      Directly<strong> restores</strong> a species or
                      habitat(s)23
                    </p>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <p lang="fr-BE">
                      Ad-hoc measure for an exception under Art. 14(1) (b), (c)
                      or (d)
                    </p>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <p lang="fr-BE">
                      <em
                        >Improve knowledge base (e.g. by research or one-off
                        surveys)</em
                      >
                    </p>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <p lang="fr-BE">
                      <em
                        >Establish monitoring programmes (of relevant
                        activities, pressures or impacts)</em
                      >
                    </p>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <p lang="fr-BE">
                      <em
                        >Assess effectiveness of the measures (through assessing
                        changes in state/impact/pressure in the marine
                        environment)</em
                      >
                    </p>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <p lang="fr-BE"><em>Not known</em></p>
                  </li>
                </ol>
              </ul>
            </ul>
